ce:section.ce:para:
Jasco FP-6600 spectrofluorometer (Tokyo, Japan) fitted with 150 W Xenon lamp was used for fluorescence measurements using 1 cm quartz cell and employing slit widths of 5 and 10 nm for the excitation and emission, respectively, sensitivity of 750 V, and a scan speed of 500 nm/min. Absorption spectra were recorded using Jasco V-6600 spectrophotometer (Tokyo) and a pair of matched quartz cells. FTIR spectra were scanned using Jasco FTIR-4200 spectrophotometer (Tokyo). Zeta potential measurement was done using a Zetasizer Nano ZS (Malvern Instruments, Ltd., Worcestershire, UK). A DX 601 drying oven (Yamato Science Co., Ltd., Tokyo), AS ONE handy UV Lamp SLUV-6 (Osaka, Japan) fitted in a dark cabinet, Mettler-Toledo pH-meter (Columbus, OH, USA), and a Personal-11 Taitec water bath (Tokyo) were used. Chem3D Ultra version 8.0 software from Cambridge software (UK) was used for molecular size calculation. ImageJ free software (National Institute of Health, Maryland, USA) (
                           https://imagej.nih.gov/ij/download.html
                        ) and RGB color detector software (Version 1.1.4, latest update 2020, freely downloaded from google play store) were used for image processing and analysis.
